      "content": "I strongly advise against recontextualizing the cause into a routine optimization, as it crosses into misleading communication that will be detected by journalists and damage your reputation more severely than admitting the truth. Explaining the technical reality honestly allows you to pivot toward concrete, verifiable steps you are taking now to prevent recurrence, which ultimately builds more trust than hiding behind ambiguity. Ultimately, a brief, honest admission paired with a rapidly executed preventative fix is the only way to maintain credibility.",
